The paper deals with a problem in database research, specifically the consistent query answering over a database that violates primary key constraints. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. The paper also presents a novel decomposition and pruning strategy that reduces the problem to smaller problems that can be solved independently, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic programming (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the approach, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper is likely to be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) as it presents a practical solution to a real-world problem.
